'''Robert Frank''' was a [[Sturmbannfuhrer]] in the [[Waffen SS]] during [[World War II]]. He was awarded the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]]. Which was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by [[Nazi Germany]] during World War II. 

Robert 'Adolf' Frank was born on the 18 October 1910, in [[Erlangen]].
He volunteered to join the [[SS-VT]] and during World War II served with the [[3 SS|SS Division ''Totenkopf'']] during the early campaignsin command of the 6th Company. He was awarded the [[Iron Cross]] II class during the [[Battle of France]] in June 1940.
He next took part in [[Operation Barbarossa]] the invasion of the [[Soviet Union]] and was awarded the Iron Cross I class in July 1941.
On the formation of the [[9 SS|9th SS Panzer Division ''Hohenstaufen'']] he took over command of the II./Battalion, 20th SS Panzergrenadier Regiment on the 4 April 1944.
He was killed in action on the 13 April 1944 near [[Tarnopol]] in the [[Ukraine]] and awarded a [[posthumous]] Knight's Cross. <ref>{{cite web|title=axis.biographical.research|url=http://www.geocities.com/~orion47/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=frontkjemper|url=http://www.frontkjemper.info/show_person.php?P_ID=633}}</ref>

